rComments: Extremely bright prof who knows her stuff, solid background in Korean lit gives her ability to make it interesting, relatable and direct and always entertaining. A little scatter-brained, but in a charming dotty-prof way. Moderate grader except for final papers, when the hammer comes out, and damn she uses it like a brutally effective bludgeon.

rComments: A fantastic prof who knows her stuff. She's smart (and she knows it) and she tries to encourage you to be enthusiastic. So long as you like Korean literature, you're golden
